history.content:
The private tutor roster linked on that page is from last semester. This semester's list is available at @13072 if you want to look at that. As for CS370, based on what others have been saying, it should be available soon (this week or next) but I'm not in the class so I can't verify. Students also use services from private tutoring companies like Edlyft and other companies are advertised on Facebook usually. 

For tutoring that's not necessarily private, you can go to HKN @13156 or COE tutoring.

<md>Hi,
I am looking for a private tutor for 61b.
The main purpose for looking for a tutor is helping me to verify I ** grasp the essence of the concepts and prepare for the followed misterm2 and final.** (I got illusion that I understand the concepts, yet the midterm1 told me I was totally wrong.)

My friend got private tutor help at https://eecs.berkeley.edu/resources/undergrads/support , however, it seems the cs370 is not enable tutor this fall and private tutor roster is also not available to access.

If anyone is interested in this, or anyone knowing where I can find the tutor help service, please let me know. 
Thank you very much!</md>
